<h4 class="heading"><span class="type">Paragraph</span></h4>
<p>On the other hand  we now know that <span class="process-math">\(\int\tan(x)\dx{x}=\ln(\sec(x)+c\)</span> and we can use this knowledge. Suppose we need to compute <span class="process-math">\(\int\frac{u}{1+u^2}\dx{u}\)</span> or <span class="process-math">\(\int\frac{u}{1-u^2}\dx{u}\text{.}\)</span> The same substitution we used to transform these into the integral <span class="process-math">\(\int\tan(x)\dx{x}\)</span> will work in reverse.</p>
<span class="incontext"><a href="section-4.html#p-64" class="internal">in-context</a></span>
